juniHttpMIB.name: juniHttpMIB

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

juniHttpMIB.contactinfo: Juniper Networks, Inc. Postal: 10 Technology Park Drive Westford MA 01886-3146 USA Tel: +1 978 589 5800 Email: mib@Juniper.net
juniHttpMIB.description: The HTTP MIB for Juniper Networks enterprise.

juniHttpDaemonRowStatus.name: juniHttpDaemonRowStatus
juniHttpDaemonRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy A corresponding entry in ifTable/ifXTable/juniIfTable is created or destroyed as a result of creating or destroying an entry in this table.

juniHttpDaemonAccessListName.name: juniHttpDaemonAccessListName
juniHttpDaemonAccessListName.description: This object is a 32 byte string that indentifies the access list.

juniHttpDaemonPort.name: juniHttpDaemonPort
juniHttpDaemonPort.description: This port number that the HTTP server will serve requests from.

juniHttpDaemonSameAddressLimit.name: juniHttpDaemonSameAddressLimit
juniHttpDaemonSameAddressLimit.description: The number of connections that the server will open for requests from the same address.

juniHttpDaemonStatsEnabled.name: juniHttpDaemonStatsEnabled
juniHttpDaemonStatsEnabled.description: Count of the number of times the server has been enabled.

juniHttpDaemonStatsDisabled.name: juniHttpDaemonStatsDisabled
juniHttpDaemonStatsDisabled.description: Count of the number of times the server has been disabled.

juniHttpDaemonStatsSameHost.name: juniHttpDaemonStatsSameHost
juniHttpDaemonStatsSameHost.description: Count of the number of times the server has not created a connection due to same host client address limit.

juniHttpDaemonStatsAccDeny.name: juniHttpDaemonStatsAccDeny
juniHttpDaemonStatsAccDeny.description: Count of the number of times the server has not created a connection due to policy access table deny.

juniHttpDaemonStatsNoResource.name: juniHttpDaemonStatsNoResource
juniHttpDaemonStatsNoResource.description: Count of the number of times the server has not created a connection due to no resources available.

juniHttpDaemonStatsCreate.name: juniHttpDaemonStatsCreate
juniHttpDaemonStatsCreate.description: Count of the number of connections created.

juniHttpDaemonStatsRemove.name: juniHttpDaemonStatsRemove
juniHttpDaemonStatsRemove.description: Count of the number of connections removed.

juniHttpDaemonStatsAged.name: juniHttpDaemonStatsAged
juniHttpDaemonStatsAged.description: Count of the number of connections removed due to connection age limits.

juniHttpDaemonStatsServed.name: juniHttpDaemonStatsServed
juniHttpDaemonStatsServed.description: Count of the number of successful html requests served.

juniHttpDaemonStatsHtmlError.name: juniHttpDaemonStatsHtmlError
juniHttpDaemonStatsHtmlError.description: Count of the number malformed html requests.

juniHttpDaemonStatsUnknownUrl.name: juniHttpDaemonStatsUnknownUrl
juniHttpDaemonStatsUnknownUrl.description: Count of the number of requests for unknown urls.

juniHttpInterfaceTable.name: juniHttpInterfaceTable
juniHttpInterfaceTable.description: The table listing the interfaces on which HTTP is enabled.

juniHttpInterfaceEntry.name: juniHttpInterfaceEntry
juniHttpInterfaceEntry.description: An entry representing an interface on which HTTP is configured.

juniHttpInterfaceIndex.name: juniHttpInterfaceIndex
juniHttpInterfaceIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the interface for which HTTP services are enabled.

juniHttpInterfaceRowStatus.name: juniHttpInterfaceRowStatus
juniHttpInterfaceRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy A corresponding entry in ifTable/ifXTable/juniIfTable is created or destroyed as a result of creating or destroying an entry in this table.

juniHttpInterfaceRedirectUrl.name: juniHttpInterfaceRedirectUrl
juniHttpInterfaceRedirectUrl.description: This object is a 64 byte string that will be used as the redirect URL when requests arrive at the HTTP server over the Ip Interface configured.

juniHttpCompliance.name: juniHttpCompliance
juniHttpCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities that implement the Juniper HTTP MIB.

juniHttpGroup.name: juniHttpGroup
juniHttpGroup.description: A collection of objects providing management of HTTP services in a Juniper product.

juniHttpDaemonStatsGroup.name: juniHttpDaemonStatsGroup
juniHttpDaemonStatsGroup.description: A collection of objects providing management of HTTP interfaces in a Juniper product.

juniHttpInterfaceGroup.name: juniHttpInterfaceGroup
juniHttpInterfaceGroup.description: A collection of objects providing management of HTTP interfaces in a Juniper product.
